SIMPLE: recuse
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: recuse
<hw>re*cuse"</hw> <pr>(r?*k?z")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧cuser</ets>, or L. <ets>recusare</ets>. See
<er>Recusant</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To refuse or reject, as
a judge; to challenge that the judge shall not try the cause.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir K. Digby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>recuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: recuse
<hw>re*cuse"</hw> <pr>(r?*k?z")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To withdraw
oneself from serving as a judge or other decision-maker in order to
avoid a real or apparent conflict of interest; -- often used with the
reflexive; <as>as, the judge <ex>recused</ex> himself due to a financial
interest in the matter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recussion</ent>⟦br⟧
